      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "SAHARA SEAKRET (6) missed the placings for the first time last week but he was drawn on the back row in a decent line-up so was far from disgraced in fifth. Came from wider than this for second the other two times he raced here. Race fit now and gets his chance. ISLAND YANKEE (7) has been racing in great heart and maintained the momentum last start when third at this venue, beaten a head. May need a bit of luck negotiating a very wide starting position but the recent consistency must be respected. CHANCETOWIN (1) has been solid from wider or second lien draws of late and should enjoy the favours from the inside barrier. BIGWHEEL BOMBA (4) made a winning return from the second line here two back and was good again when placed last time. Contender.",
